Below is one way to stop dumping the raw JSON into your description and instead build a human-readable string out of your CSI-matrix before you concatenate it into the overall RQST_DESC. In your popup component, where you currently do:

ts
Copy
Edit
// old
this.createRequest(item, requestItemsLength, counter, matrixArray);
you can map your array of objects into a flat, semicolon-separated, “CSI ID: … , Total Records: …” string:

ts
Copy
Edit
// build a human-readable CSI Matrix string
const csiMatrixDesc: string = matrixArray
  .map(m =>
    `CSI ID: ${m.csi_desc || m.CSI_ID}, ` +
    `Total Records: ${m.TOTAL_REC_CNT}, ` +
    `Total Exceptions: ${m.TOTAL_EXCPN_CNT}, ` +
    `Exception %: ${m.TOTAL_EXCPN_PCT}`
  )
  .join('; ');

this.createRequest(item, requestItemsLength, counter, csiMatrixDesc);
Then change your createRequest signature so it takes that already-formatted string instead of an any[]:

diff
Copy
Edit
@@ permit-to-build-popup.component.ts
-  async createRequest(selectedRequestItem: any,
-                      requestItemsLength: number,
-                      counter: number,
-                      csiMatrix: any[]) {
+  async createRequest(selectedRequestItem: any,
+                      requestItemsLength: number,
+                      counter: number,
+                      csiMatrixDesc: string) {

    console.log(
      `Permit – Variables: SelectedRequestItem=${JSON.stringify(selectedRequestItem)}, ` +
      `RequestItemsLength=${requestItemsLength}, Counter=${counter}`
    );

    // … build your payload …

-   + '; Maker Comments: ' + this.makerComments
-   + '; CSI Matrix: ' + JSON.stringify(csiMatrix);
+   + '; Maker Comments: ' + this.makerComments
+   + '; CSI Matrix: ' + csiMatrixDesc;
    
    // … send to backend …
  }
Now your RQST_DESC will look like:

yaml
Copy
Edit
Permit To Deploy request for Rule Deployment Id: 2358153;
Rule Desc: Test am59508 060925;
Rationalized CDE Name: myCDE;
Sending System ID: 165366;
Product: Commercial Loans;
Maker Comments: test;
CSI Matrix: CSI ID: 165366, Total Records: 2000, Total Exceptions: 20, Exception %: 1.0000; CSI ID: 752, Total Records: 1000, Total Exceptions: 10, Exception %: 1.0000
which is far more readable than the raw JSON blob.

